INSERT INTO `faq` VALUES (1,4,'How long does it take for my application to be processed and to get a reply?','All applicants will be informed of their application outcome via applicantsÕ email and SIM applicant portal within one month of course commencement. Verbal offers of admission will not be made nor accepted. The Admissions Committee selects students for admission into the programme based on individual merits. Possession of one or more of the qualifications listed does not guarantee automatic entry to the programme.','','','enabled',1616638690,2,1616721404,1),(2,4,'Can SIM full-time international students holding Student\'s Pass work in Singapore?','No.  Under the Immigration & Checkpoints Authority\'s regulations, full-time international students studying in any Approved Private Educational Institutions are not allowed to engage in any form of paid or unpaid employment or be in any business during the duration of the Student\'s Pass.  This applies to all international students studying in SIM Global Education.','','','enabled',1616638690,2,1616721411,1),(3,4,'Can CPF be used for paying the programme fees?','No. Singapore Institute of Management is a private education institution. Only programme fees at public tertiary institutions, like NTU, NUS, SMU, SUSS and the local polytechnics can be paid using CPF.','','','enabled',1616638690,2,1616721420,1),(4,1,'Can I come on behalf of my son/daughter/friend to show the original documents for verification?','Yes, you may come on behalf of another person for document verification process.  Please bring along all the original required documents.','','','enabled',1616638690,2,1616721382,1),(5,1,'What is the programme structure and duration? (UOL Diplomas for Graduate)','Students take 4 full courses in the one-year Diploma for Graduates. The structure varies depending on the specialisation of the Diploma. At the end of the academic year, students sit for the University of London examinations.\r\nThe 4 full courses may be made up of Foundation courses and Further courses. Unlike the BSc degrees where the Foundation courses form the pre-requisites for Further courses, there are no pre-requisites in the Diploma for Graduates programme. Eg. Students are expected to take the Introduction to Economics examination a few days away from the Econometrics exam. Both these courses are compulsory in the Diploma for Graduates in Economics.\r\nWhen there is a choice of courses, refer to the Selection Groups for the units available at SIM, from which students can choose their electives.\r\nThe above applies to UOL Diplomas for Graduate programmes only.','','','enabled',1616638690,2,1616721388,1),(6,NULL,'How are applicants selected? Are interviews or tests a part of the selection process?','Selection is done by an Academic Committee (AC).  Admission is not automatic.  Only students who can demonstrate through their application that they are likely to perform at a high level and cope with the demands of the programme will be accepted.  There are no admission tests.  However, interviews may be conducted at the discretion of the University.','',NULL,'enabled',1616638690,2,1616638690,2),(7,1,'Where do I buy my textbooks?','You can buy your textbooks from the SIM-POPULAR bookshops located in SIM Headquarters. Please refer to your booklist posted in SIMConnect in the RMIT Booklist folder under the Resources tab. Booklist is made available one week before semester commencement.','','','enabled',1616638690,2,1616721396,1),(13,1,'How do I login to SIMConnect?','Please go to  https://simconnect.simge.edu.sg and use your MyMail email address and WiFi Password to sign in to SIMConnect.\r\nUnless you are matriculated, you would not have received your MyMail email address and WiFi password. You can enquire about your matriculation status through Student Services.','\"\"','','enabled',1619347441,3,1619347441,3),(14,4,'Can my child / I enrol in SIM with NITEC qualification?','Those with NITEC qualification may be considered for our SIM Foundation programmes.\r\n\r\nThe admission criteria for applicant with NITEC qualification are:\r\n1) overall GPA of 3.5 or better; AND\r\n2) GCE \'O\' level (grade C6 or better) or GCE \'NA\' level (grade A1 or A2) pass in English (first language)\r\n\r\nDepending on your NITEC certificate, you may choose from one of the following SIM Foundation programmes:\r\n1) Management Foundation Studies (MFS)\r\n - Applicable to NITEC certificate in Business Services, Finance Services, Logistics Services, Retail Services, and Travel and Tourism Services.\r\n2) Information Technology Foundation Studies (ITFS)\r\n- Applicable to NITEC certificate in Communication Technology, Digital Animation, Digital Audio and Video Production, Digital Media Design, Digital Media Design (Interactive Media / Digital Video Effects), Info-Communications Technology, Info-Communications Technology (Cloud Computing / Mobile Networks & Applications / Mobile Systems & Services / Networking & Systems Administration), and Security Technology.\r\n','\"\"','','enabled',1619347678,1,1619347678,1),(15,4,'Is SIM registered with MOE?','Singapore Institute of Management (SIM) is registered with the Council for Private Education (CPE) under the Enhanced Registration Framework (ERF), as set out under the Private Education Act and the Private Education Regulations.  CPE is a statutory board established under the Ministry of Education on 1 Dec 2009.  From 03 October 2016, the Council for Private Education became part of a new statutory board - SkillsFuture Singapore (SSG).  Under the new structure, the SSG Board appointed the Committee for Private Education (CPE) to carry out its functions and powers relating to private education under the Private Education Act.\r\n\r\nAll Private Education Institutions (PEIs) are required to comply with the regulations under the Act in order to continue operations.\r\n\r\nSIM is also given the EduTrust award for having achieved satisfactory to commendable performance in key areas of management and the provision of educational services.\r\n\r\nFor more details, you can refer to the CPE website at https://www.ssg-wsg.gov.sg.','\"\"','','enabled',1619347940,1,1619347940,1),(16,4,'How do I apply for SIM GE programme?','Majority of the programme applications are to be submitted online. International students can only apply for full-time programme as per Immigration and Checkpoints Authority (ICA) requirements. SIM GE will provide assistance to submit Student\'s Pass application.\r\n\r\nPlease refer to the website to apply for the specific programme you are interested in.\r\n\r\n\r\nLocal Applicants\r\nApplication fee must be made online with MasterCard/Visa Credit Card or eNETS. Other modes of payment are not accepted.\r\n\r\nAll original documents must be presented for verification at Blk A Level 2, Student Recruitment & Payment Office, SIM HQ 461 Clementi Road, Singapore 599491 within 7 days after submission or before closing date for application, whichever is earlier.\r\n\r\n\r\nInternational Applicants\r\nApplication fee must be made online with MasterCard/Visa Credit Card. Other modes of payment are not accepted. \r\n\r\nAfter payment, please proceed to complete the Student\'s Pass application.\r\n\r\nYou may submit your documents by the following options:\r\n1) Bring along the ORIGINAL documents for verification at SIM’s Student Recruitment Centre,\r\n    BLK A  Level 2 at SIM Headquarters, 461 Clementi Road, Singapore 599491\r\nOR\r\n2) Mail by courier the original notarized documents to:\r\n    Admissions Department (SIM GE)\r\n    SIM Headquarters\r\n    461 Clementi Road\r\n    Singapore 599491','\"\"','','enabled',1619347975,1,1619347975,1),(17,4,'Can I apply to SIM GE with a Diploma/Advanced Diploma from private schools?','Prospective students should have diploma from the local polytechnics in Singapore or SIM Diploma to meet the general admission requirements for an undergraduate programme. Selection of students is done by an Admissions Committee and is competitive. The final decision on admission rests with the respective universities. Students with Diploma/Advanced Diploma from private schools may apply and be considered on a case by case basis.  Other requirements such as IELTS/TOEFL may apply.','\"\"','','enabled',1619348155,1,1619348155,1),(18,4,'Can my child / I enrol in SIM with GCE \'N\' Level qualification?','We do not have any programmes catered to students with GCE \'N\' Level qualification.','\"\"','','enabled',1619348254,1,1619348254,1),(19,4,'Can I check the status of my application online?','All applicants will be informed of their application outcome via email and SIMConnect applicant portal within one month of course commencement.  Verbal offers of admission will not be made nor accepted.','\"\"','','enabled',1619348337,1,1619348337,1),(20,4,'What are the available financial assistance schemes?','You may obtain study loans from the following financial institutions:\r\n\r\nMaybank\r\nTel: 1800 629 2265\r\nWebsite: http://www.maybank2u.com.sg\r\n\r\nPOSB\r\nTel: 6333 0033\r\nWebsite: http://www.posb.com.sg\r\n\r\nRHB Bank Berhad\r\nTel: 1800 323 0100\r\nWebsite: http://www.rhbbank.com.sg\r\n\r\nCIMB Bank\r\nTel: 6333 7777\r\nWebsite: http://www.cimbbank.com.sg\r\n\r\nOCBC Bank\r\nTel: 1800 363 3333\r\nWebsite: http://www.frankbyocbc.com\r\n\r\nPlease contact the above institutions directly if you wish to obtain a loan.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nInterest-Free Instalment Plans\r\nWhen you charge above S$500 to your OCBC Visa/MasterCard, you can enjoy interest-free instalments of six or 12-months. Terms and conditions apply.\r\n\r\nFor more information, please call:\r\n\r\nOCBC\r\nTel: 1800 363 3333\r\nWebsite: http://www.ocbc.com.sg','\"\"','','enabled',1619348428,1,1619348428,1),(21,4,'My application is unsuccessful. How can I appeal for admission?','You may submit an appeal by writing in to us at study@sim.edu.sg with reasons and supporting documents (if any).\r\n\r\nSubmission of appeals should be done as soon as possible to allow Admissions sufficient time to consider your appeal.','\"\"','','enabled',1619348489,1,1619348489,1),(22,4,'How do I collect my Student\'s Pass?','You must make an e-appointment with ICA before collecting your Student\'s Pass. Please refer to the instruction as stipulated on your In-Principle Approval letter.\r\n','\"\"','','enabled',1619348546,1,1619348546,1),(23,4,'What is the duration of coverage for the fee protection scheme and medical insurance?','The coverage applies to the entire duration of your studies in SIM.','\"\"','','enabled',1619348580,1,1619348580,1),(24,4,'Does SIM offer job placements to students after their studies?','Our Career Development Office helps students develop and identify career objectives through professional programmes that enhance self-awareness and career skills. We provide the following professional programmes to students:\r\n- Career workshops\r\n- Career guidance\r\n- Career events\r\n- Internship and job opportunities','\"\"','','enabled',1619348675,1,1619348675,1),(25,4,'Can I defer from the programme whilst in the midst of doing the programme?','Students have to apply for leave of absence from the Student Services Centre.  Application will be subjected to the University\'s consideration and approval.','\"\"','','enabled',1619348737,1,1619348737,1),(26,4,'Can I pursue a part-time programme while serving National Service (NS)?\r\n','You may pursue a part-time programme while serving National Service (NS) if you are able to attend classes/lectures in the evenings and weekends.','\"\"','','enabled',1619348816,1,1619348816,1),(27,4,'I am in my final semester of my diploma, can I apply for the programme which is commencing in the coming intake?','Yes, you may submit an application with all your completed semester results whilst attending your final semester.  However, you are required to submit your final semester results once it is available. \r\n\r\nPlease note that the above does not apply to all programmes.  For clarifications, please call our Recruitment Hotline at 6248 9746.','\"\"','','enabled',1619348949,1,1619348949,1),(28,4,'What are the programmes available for GCE \'A\' level holders?','Those with GCE \'A\' level qualification can choose programmes from the following awarding Universities / Institutions:\r\n\r\nUniversity of London\r\nRMIT University\r\nUniversity of Wollongong\r\nUniversity at Buffalo, the State University of New York\r\n\r\nUniversity of Stirling\r\n\r\nSIM Global Education\r\nYou may refer to our website for the list of programmes offered and admission criteria.','\"\"','','enabled',1619349005,1,1619349005,1),(29,4,'Do I need to get a sponsor for my Student\'s Pass application?','You do not have to get a sponsor. SIM will be your sponsor for Student\'s Pass.','\"\"','','enabled',1619349042,1,1619349042,1),(30,4,'Does SIM offer any scholarships?','Yes, new international students with exemplary academic results may apply for the SIM Global Education (SIM GE) Scholarship when they enrol for the Diploma programmes awarded by SIM GE.\r\n\r\nWe also offer scholarships to outstanding local and international students to pursue bachelor\'s degree programmes at SIM GE.','\"\"','','enabled',1619349137,1,1619349137,1),(31,4,'Will the application fee be refunded if my application is unsuccessful?','Application fee is neither refundable nor transferable.','\"\"','','enabled',1619349182,1,1619349182,1),(32,4,'How can I pay the application fee?','Application fee must be made online with MasterCard/Visa Credit Card or eNETS. Other modes of payment are not accepted.','\"\"','','enabled',1619349243,1,1619349243,1),(33,4,'Can I apply with provisional results?','SIM do not accept predicted or provisional results. Applicants must apply with their official results.','\"\"','','enabled',1619349293,1,1619583815,2),(34,4,'I am not sure which programme I prefer. Can I apply for more than one programme?','Yes, you can apply for as many programmes as you wish. However, for every application made, a separate application fee is applicable.\r\n\r\nThe exception is the degrees developed and awarded by the University at Buffalo, The State University of New York, where only one application is allowed.\r\n\r\nNote that while you can apply for more than one programme, you are allowed to pursue only one qualification-based programme at any one time.','\"\"','','enabled',1619349354,1,1619349354,1),(35,4,'How will I know if my Student\'s Pass application is successful?','SIM will notify you via Mymail email once Immigration and Checkpoint Authority (ICA) releases your payment of Issuance fee notification.  After payment is made please download your  In-Principle Approval (IPA) letter.  Please follow all instructions on the letter carefully and look out for our email.','\"\"','','enabled',1619349389,1,1619349389,1);
