ke\\r\\nStandard Entry (3-year): Apr 2021 \\u2013 Mar 2024\\r\\n\\r\\nJul 2020 Intake\\r\\nStandard Entry (3-year): Jul 2021 \\u2013 Jun 2024\\r\\n\\r\\nOct 2020 Intake\\r\\nStandard Entry (3-year): Oct 2021 \\u2013 Sep 2024\\r\\n\\r\\nNote: The completion date may vary depending on the exemptions (if any) granted.\",\"scholarships_award\":\"Top graduands from the programme are eligible to receive awards from Info-communications Media Development Authority (IMDA).\\r\\nSIM scholarships are available\",\"overview\":\"Developed and awarded by University of Wollongong, Australia.\\r\\n\\r\\nUOW has achieved a 5-star rating in the 2018 Good Universities Guide for Guide for Overall experience; Skills development; Student support; Teaching quality; Learning resources and Learner engagement.\\r\\n\\r\\nYou can find UOW\\u2019s awards at https:\\/\\/www.uow.edu.au\\/about\\/awards\\/index.html\\r\\n\\r\\nA UOW Information Technology degree will provide you with the skills to make a company more productive and efficient through the use of IT. The degree has a solid foundation in theory, analysis, design, and implementation. These core skills are extended into a range of key areas, including systems administration, data and process management, web development and aspects of software engineering.\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/sim003452.jpg\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616638690,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619055625,\"updated_by\":3}',3,1619055625),(24,1,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":1,\"name\":\"University of Wollongong (UOW)\",\"description\":\"The University of Wollongong, in 40 years since its independence, has grown from a small college serving local industry to an international university, renowned for the quality of its research and teaching. It has become a benchmark for a new generation of universities. Over 35,000 students are studying UOW degrees across nine campuses throughout Australia and in Malaysia and Dubai, with education partnerships in Singapore and Hong Kong. \\r\\n\\r\\nUOW attracts students from more than 140 countries. UOW is strongly focused on interdisciplinary research that has a real impact on our lives and contributes to solving global challenges. To achieve that, UOW\'s key research institutes have developed strong partnerships and collaborations with government and non-government organisations, corporations, universities and research institutes in Australia and around the world. \\r\\n\\r\\nFor more and updated details, visit their website at www.uow.edu.au\",\"continent\":\"australia\",\"highlights\":\"SIM Global Education is UOW\'s only partner in Singapore for its IT degree programmes\\r\\nOver 3000 degrees conferred from the UOW-SIM programmes since partnership started in 2005\\r\\nTaught by top academics and professors from UOW with industry experience\",\"certifications\":\"7  available programmes as below.\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time and Part-Time:\\r\\nBachelor of Computer Science (Digital Systems Security)\\r\\nBachelor of Computer Science (Cyber Security)\\r\\n\\r\\nFull Time:\\r\\nBachelor of Psychological Science\\r\\nBachelor of Computer Science (Game and Mobile Development)\\r\\nBachelor of Computer Science (Big Data)\\r\\nBachelor of Business Information Systems.\\r\\n\\r\\nPart-Time:\\r\\nBachelor of Information Technology\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/university-of-wollongong-logo.png\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616638690,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619056061,\"updated_by\":3}',3,1619056061),(25,1,'common\\models\\Events','events','update','{\"id\":1,\"school_id\":4,\"session\":\"2021Q2\",\"name\":\"SIM Open House\",\"type\":\"orientation\",\"description\":\"SIM Open House\",\"venue\":\"On-Campus & Online\",\"start_at\":1618245960,