n the maximum period.\\r\\n\\r\\nSIM reserves the right to recommend and withdraw a student who cannot cope with the demands of the programme, especially when the student\\u2019s pass has expired.\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum Class Size\\r\\nMinimum class size to commence: 25 students. Students will be informed within 30 days before class commences.\",\"admission_criteria\":\"Entry Requirements\\r\\nGCE A-level, IB diploma, or other equivalent pre-university certifications, or\\r\\nPolytechnic diploma or equivalent, or\\r\\nSIM GE\\u2019s foundation programme, namely, Information Technology Foundation Studies (ITFS)\\r\\n*Applicants who do not meet the direct academic entry requirement are required to complete Information Technology Foundation Studies (ITFS) programme. Click here for details of the ITFS programme.\\r\\n\\r\\nInternational Applicants (full-time)\\r\\nInternational applicants will be assessed on the qualification\\u2019s equivalent to the GCE \\u2018A\\u2019 level examinations.\\r\\n\\r\\nRefer to details on qualifications listed in the International Student Prospectus. Alternatively, you may click here for the list of overseas qualifications.\\r\\n\\r\\nEnglish Language Requirement\\r\\nGCE \\u2018O\\u2019 level credit pass (Grade 1 to 6) in English (as a first language); or\\r\\nIELTS with an overall score of at least 5.5; or\\r\\nTOEFL score of at least 550 (paper-based) or 213 (computer-based) plus 4 in the Test of Written English (TWE) or 59 (iBT); or\\r\\nAn equivalent English language qualification.\\r\\nApplicants who do not meet the English language requirement would need to undergo the Certificate in English Language (CEL) programme before enrolment in the Diploma programme.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe duration of the CEL programme depends on the applicant\\u2019s English language proficiency level.\\r\\n\\r\\nApplicants can sit for an English Placement Test conducted by SIM to determine their English language proficiency level. Click here for details of the CEL programme\\r\\n\\r\\nNotes:\\r\\n\\r\\nIELTS or TOEFL scores must be less than two years at point of enrolment.\\r\\nThe SIM English Placement Test results will be valid for one year from the date of the test.\",\"fees\":\"S$9,630 (for 2021 intake)\\r\\n\\r\\nApplication Fee applies\\r\\n\\r\\nAll fees inclusive of prevailing GST.\",\"exemptions\":\"Nil\",\"profiles\":\"Average teacher-student ratio 1:41\",\"assessments_exams\":\"Assessment and Exams\\r\\nEach module is assessed through multiple continuous assessments.\\r\\nContinuous assessments may include practical assessment, class tests, discussions, presentations, group and individual assignments.\\r\\n\\r\\nPromotion\\r\\nTo attain a pass for each module, students must achieve overall minimum GPA of 1.0 (grade \\u2018D\\u2019).\\r\\n\\r\\nAttendance Requirement\\r\\n75% attendance to sit for exams.\\r\\n\\r\\nStudent\\u2019s Pass holders: at least 90% attendance in any month of the course (as required by the Singapore Immigration Checkpoint Authority).\\r\\n\\r\\nGraduation \\r\\nStudents must successfully complete and pass all 8 modules. Graduating students will be awarded with a Diploma from SIM\",\"entry_qualification\":\"diploma\",\"application\":\"Full-time \\u2013 Oct 2021 Intake\\r\\nLocal Applicants\\r\\nNow till 22 Aug 2021\\r\\nInternational Applicants\\r\\nNow till 15 Aug 2021\",\"course_start_end_date\":\"Intake Month(s)\\r\\nFull-time: Apr, Oct\\r\\n2 intakes per year: April & October\\r\\nOctober intake: 1 October 2021 to 30 September 2022\",\"scholarships_award\":\"Nil\",\"overview\":\"Developed and awarded by the Singapore Institute of Management, Singapore\\r\\n\\r\\nThis programme is designed to equip you with a strong understanding of core skills that are relevant to the IT industry, especially skills needed for developing broad-based information systems which support business needs and achieve competitive advantage.\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/11\\/SIM1.jpg\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619245601,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619247496,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619247496),(29,19,'common\\models\\Courses','courses','create','{\"id\":19,\"school_id\":1,\"name\":\"Bachelor of Computer Science (Digital Systems Security)\",\"mode_of_study\":\"part_time_and_full_time\",\"disciplines\":\"IT and Computer Science\",\"sub_disciplines\":\"Digital Systems Security\",\"academic_level\":\"Bachelor\",\"introduction\":\"Fight Cyber-crime with Digital Security Skills\\r\\nAs we expand our digital lives, information is crossing borders and networks at a speed and volume that is hard to comprehend. The security of our personal and financial information has hence become a key issue for individuals, industry and government.\\r\\n\\r\\nCyber-crime has also posed a real and persistent threat to any organisation whose online system has to offer convenient access to legitimate users, and yet be secure enough to prevent hacking and theft.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe knowledge, research and strategic thinking skills developed through the Digital Systems Security programme are needed to succeed in this rapidly growing industry, ensuring privacy and preventing crimes.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nAccreditations\\r\\nAustralian Computer Society (ACS)\\r\\n\\r\\nThe ACS has mutual recognition of qualifications with:\\r\\n\\r\\nSingapore Computer Society\\r\\nInternational Federation of Information Processing\\r\\nSouth East Asia Regional Computer Confederation\\r\\nMalaysia National Computer Confederation\\r\\nSeoul Accord \\u2013 mutual recognition between ABEEK (Korea), ABET (US), BCS (UK), CIPS (Canada), HKIE (HK and China), IEET (Taiwan), JABEE (Japan)\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nStudy Opportunities (offered by UOW in Australia)\\r\\nStudents in the UOW programme at SIM are eligible to transfer to Wollongong campus but subject to separate application and enrolment process. Graduates can apply to enrol in the Bachelor of Computer Science (Hons) programme at Wollongong campus.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nCareer Prospects\\r\\nPotential career includes:\\r\\n\\r\\ne-Security Manager, providing secured access to enterprise information over the Web from both inside and outside corporate networks for e-commerce enterprises\\r\\nCryptographer, developing strong encryption products for Internet communication in business, financial institutions, government and other major organisations\\r\\nDatabase Security Administrator, ensuring identification and authentication for a wide range of corporations\\r\\nSoftware Architect\\r\\nEntrepreneur for e-Security businesses\\r\\nIT Auditor\\r\\nChief Security Officer\\r\\nDesigner and developer of secured hardware systems for financial services, defence, government and media\\r\\netc.\",\"programme_structure\":\"Teaching Faculty\\r\\nThis programme is taught in Singapore by local academics and\\/or practitioners as well as UOW academics.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nMode of Delivery\\r\\nThe course is intensive and demanding but rewarding and achievable.\\r\\n\\r\\nClasses include face-to-face lectures, tutorials and lab sessions.\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time\\r\\nClasses are typically in 3-hour blocks: 8:30 \\u2013 11:30am, 12noon \\u2013 3pm, or 3:30 \\u2013 6:30pm and may be held on Saturday mornings and\\/or afternoons (subject to timetable).\\r\\n\\r\\nPart-Time\\r\\nClasses are typically in 3-hour blocks: Weekdays (7-10pm) and may be held on Saturday mornings and\\/or afternoon (subject to timetable).\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nClasses delivered by UOW academics are conducted in an intensive mode \\u2013 a continuous block of seven days for each module.\\r\\n\\r\\nStudents typically study two modules per term. Each year comprises of 4 terms.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nProgramme Structure\\r\\nTo be awarded the Bachelor of Computer Science (Digital Systems Security), student must complete, or exempted from completing (depending on their advanced standing status), a total of 23 modules comprising of core modules, elective modules and one final year project.\\r\\n\\r\\nCore Modules List\\r\\n\\r\\nNetworks and Communications\\r\\nHuman Computer Interaction\\r\\nProgramming Fundamentals\\r\\nProblem Solving\\r\\nSystem Analysis\\r\\nData Management & Security\\r\\nObject Oriented Design & Programming\\r\\nIntroduction to Web Technology\\r\\nIT Project Management\\r\\nSoftware Development Methodologies*\\r\\nMathematics for Computer Science\\r\\nAlgorithms & Data Structures\\r\\nAdvanced Programming\\r\\nDatabase Systems\\r\\nCryptography and Secure Applications*\\r\\nNetwork Security*\\r\\nSystem Security*\\r\\nMulticore and GPU programming*\\r\\nElectives List\\r\\n\\r\\nDistributed Systems and Cloud Computing*\\r\\nBig Data Mining Techniques and Implementation*\\r\\nContemporary Topics in Security*\\r\\nCybersecurity*\\r\\nEthical Hacking*\\r\\nWeb Server Programming*\\r\\nSystems Administration*\\r\\nBig Data Management*\\r\\nData Mining and Knowledge Discovery*\\r\\nDatabase Performance Tuning*\\r\\nMobile Multimedia\\r\\nInteractive Computer Graphics*\\r\\nGame Engine Essentials*\\r\\n3D Modelling and Animation*\\r\\nBusiness Process Management*\\r\\nStrategic eBusiness Solutions\\r\\nFrontend Web Programming\\r\\nPrinciples of eBusiness\\r\\nManagement Information Systems*\\r\\nKnowledge & Information Engineering\\r\\nIntroduction to Management\\r\\nAccounting Fundamentals in Society\\r\\nBusiness Communications\\r\\nMarketing Principles\\r\\nAccounting in Organisations\\r\\nManaging Human Resources\\r\\nOrganisational Behaviour\\r\\nOrganisational Analysis\\r\\nManagement of Change\\r\\nStatistics for Business\\r\\nEconomic Essentials for Business\\r\\nIndustry and Trade in Asia\\r\\nStrategic Systems Management\\r\\nMobile Application Development\\r\\nFundamental Programming with Python\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nPending Teach-out \\r\\n\\r\\n\\u2022 Algorithms and Problem Solving\\r\\n\\u2022 Applied Programming\\r\\n\\u2022 Databases\\r\\n\\u2022 Discrete Mathematics\\r\\n\\u2022 Interacting Systems\\r\\n\\u2022 Internet Technologies\\r\\n\\u2022 Introduction to W3 Technologies\\r\\n\\u2022 Object and Generic Programming in C++\\r\\n\\u2022 Procedural Programming\\r\\n\\u2022 Professional Practice and Ethics\\r\\n\\u2022 Security Engineering\\r\\n\\u2022 Software Development Methods and Tools\\r\\n\\u2022 Systems\\r\\n\\u2022 Systems Development\\r\\n\\u2022 Understanding Variation and Uncertainty\\r\\n\\r\\n1 Final Year Project\\r\\n* modules are taught by UOW Academics, supported by local tutors.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor module descriptions, click HERE.\\r\\nFor detailed programme structure, click HERE.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe above modules are subject to changes by the university and subject to availability. Not all modules will be offered every term.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nCandidature Period\\r\\nMaximum 3 times the duration for completion under a standard full-time load, subject to meeting ongoing course progression rules.\\r\\n\\r\\nThere will not be any refund should the student fail to complete the programme within the maximum allowed period. Students who exceed their candidature period will not be allowed to remain in the programme, unless an extension to the candidature period is approved by the University.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum Class Size\\r\\nMinimum class size to commence: 24 students\\r\\n\\r\\nIn the event that the minimum number is not met, the intake may not commence. The student shall be informed within one month before programme commencement.\",\"admission_criteria\":\"Entry Requirements\\r\\n3 GCE \\u2018A\\u2019 level \\/ 3 H2 passes plus 1 H1 pass with a minimum aggregate of 9 points where A=5, B=4, C=3, D=2, E=1 (for H1 apply half the value)*\\r\\nDiploma: 3-year diploma from local polytechnic or its equivalent.\\r\\n*Minimum Aggregate scores in the qualifications mentioned are required for entry and will be assessed by UOW.\\r\\n\\r\\nApplicants may be admitted to different credit exemptions based on their academic results.\\r\\nFor information on Overseas Qualifications, click HERE\\r\\n\\r\\nEnglish Proficiency Requirements\\r\\nApplicants with international qualification must meet the University\\u2019s English requirement:\\r\\n\\r\\nIELTS 6.0 (with no band less than 6.0); or\\r\\nTOEFL 70 (iBT) with at least 18 for Reading & Writing and at least 17 for Speaking & Listening; or\\r\\nPearson Test score of at least 54 for English (Academic) (with at least 54 for Reading & Writing\\r\\nand at least 47 for Speaking & Listening) or equivalent\",\"fees\":\"Full Programme (3 years): S$33,384.00 for 23 modules, payable over 12 terms\\r\\n\\r\\nWith credit exemption:\\r\\n0.5 Year credit exemption: S$29,104.00 for 19 modules, payable over 10 terms\\r\\n1 Year credit exemption   : S$24,824.00 for 15 modules, payable over 8 terms\\r\\n1.5 Year credit exemption: S$20,544.00 for 11 modules, payable over 6 terms\\r\\n\\r\\nModules delivered by local academics : S$1,070.00 per module\\r\\nModules delivered by UOW academics: S$2,033.00 per module\\r\\nFinal Year Project (FYP)                       : S$4,066.00 per module\\r\\n\\r\\nFees quoted are valid for Jul 2021 intakes only.\\r\\nAbove fees exclude textbooks and repeat fees of failed module. Not all modules will be offered in every term.\\r\\nFirst term fees payable upon acceptance of offer. Subsequent term fees payable before commencement of the term.\\r\\nAll fees inclusive of prevailing GST.\\r\\nApplication Fee applies\",\"exemptions\":\"Exemption Eligibility\\r\\nExemptions are normally granted automatically to students with relevant background. Block exemptions may be granted to students with relevant diplomas from the local polytechnics and universities.\\r\\n\\r\\nAll modules previously studied will be evaluated and compared with the requirements of the student\\u2019s programme of study and a block exemption granted where appropriate.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo obtain maximum credit exemption, applicants must have GPA of 2.0 or more (out of 4.0). Applicants with GPA below 2.0 will be assessed on a case-by-case basis.\",\"profiles\":\"Profiles\\r\\nLecturers & Teaching Modules\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time\\r\\n\\r\\nAverage teacher-student ratio 1:55\\r\\n\\r\\nPart-Time\\r\\n\\r\\nAverage teacher-student ratio 1:26\",\"assessments_exams\":\"Students are normally assessed by continuous assessments in the following form:\\r\\n\\r\\nAssignments\\r\\nClass tests\\r\\nLaboratory exercises\\r\\nPractical laboratory tests\\r\\nPresentations\\r\\nProjects\\r\\nTutorial exercises\\r\\nSome assignments and presentations will be group-based. Assessment may have a minimum achievement requirement necessary to pass the module.\\r\\n\\r\\nMost modules have a final examination at the end of term.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nAcademic Progress\\r\\nStudents are to pass all modules within the current year of study before proceeding to the next year of study.  For modules with pre-requisites, students may be required to meet the pre-requisites before undertaking the modules.\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nAttendance requirement\\r\\nFull-Time\\r\\nLocal students: 80%\\r\\nInternational students: 90%\\r\\n \\r\\nPart-Time\\r\\n80%\\r\\n\\r\\n \\r\\n\\r\\nAward & Graduation\\r\\nStudents who successfully complete all academic requirements of the programme will be awarded the Bachelor of Computer Science (Digital Systems Security) by the University of Wollongong, Australia.\\r\\n\\r\\nA degree conferral ceremony will be held in Singapore.\",\"entry_qualification\":\"diploma\",\"application\":\"Full-Time \\/ Part-Time\\r\\n\\r\\n4 intakes a year (Jan, Apr, Jul & Oct)\\r\\n\\r\\nJan 2021 Intake\\r\\nStandard Entry (3-year): Jan 2021 \\u2013 Dec 2023\\r\\n\\r\\nApr 2021 Intake\\r\\nStandard Entry (3-year): Apr 2021 \\u2013 Mar 2024\\r\\n\\r\\nJul 2021 Intake\\r\\nStandard Entry (3-year): Jul 2021 \\u2013 Jun 2024\\r\\n\\r\\nOct 2021 Intake\\r\\nStandard Entry (3-year): Oct 2021 \\u2013 Sep 2024\\r\\n\\r\\nNote: The completion date may vary depending on the exemptions (if any) granted.\",\"course_start_end_date\":\"Intake Month(s)\\r\\nFull-time: Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct\\r\\nPart-time: Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct\",\"scholarships_award\":\"Top graduands from the programme are eligible to receive awards from Centre for Strategic Infocomm Technologies (CSIT) and Info-communications Media Development Authority (IMDA).\\r\\nCSIT Scholarship (refer to CSIT website for more details)\\r\\nSIM scholarships are available\",\"overview\":\"Developed and awarded by University of Wollongong, Australia.\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/sim003452.jpg\",\"tags\":\"[\\\"uow\\\",\\\"dss\\\"]\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619329406,\"created_by\":3,\"updated_at\":1619329406,\"updated_by\":3}',3,1619329406),(30,13,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":13,\"school_id\":1,\"question\":\"How do I login to SIMConnect?\",\"answer\":\"Please go to  https:\\/\\/simconnect.simge.edu.sg and use your MyMail email address and WiFi Password to sign in to SIMConnect.\\r\\nUnless you are matriculated, you would not have received your MyMail email address and WiFi password. You can enquire about your matriculation status through Student Services.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619347441,\"created_by\":3,\"updated_at\":1619347441,\"updated_by\":3}',3,1619347441),(31,14,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":14,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Can my child \\/ I enrol in SIM with NITEC qualification?\",\"answer\":\"Those with NITEC qualification may be considered for our SIM Foundation programmes.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe admission criteria for applicant with NITEC qualification are:\\r\\n1) overall GPA of 3.5 or better; AND\\r\\n2) GCE \'O\' level (grade C6 or better) or GCE \'NA\' level (grade A1 or A2) pass in English (first language)\\r\\n\\r\\nDepending on your NITEC certificate, you may choose from one of the following SIM Foundation programmes:\\r\\n1) Management Foundation Studies (MFS)\\r\\n - Applicable to NITEC certificate in Business Services, Finance Services, Logistics Services, Retail Services, and Travel and Tourism Services.\\r\\n2) Information Technology Foundation Studies (ITFS)\\r\\n- Applicable to NITEC certificate in Communication Technology, Digital Animation, Digital Audio and Video Production, Digital Media Design, Digital Media Design (Interactive Media \\/ Digital Video Effects), Info-Communications Technology, Info-Communications Technology (Cloud Computing \\/ Mobile Networks & Applications \\/ Mobile Systems & Services \\/ Networking & Systems Administration), and Security Technology.\\r\\n\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619347678,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619347678,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619347678),(32,15,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":15,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Is SIM registered with MOE?\",\"answer\":\"Singapore Institute of Management (SIM) is registered with the Council for Private Education (CPE) under the Enhanced Registration Framework (ERF), as set out under the Private Education Act and the Private Education Regulations.  CPE is a statutory board established under the Ministry of Education on 1 Dec 2009.  From 03 October 2016, the Council for Private Education became part of a new statutory board - SkillsFuture Singapore (SSG).  Under the new structure, the SSG Board appointed the Committee for Private Education (CPE) to carry out its functions and powers relating to private education under the Private Education Act.\\r\\n\\r\\nAll Private Education Institutions (PEIs) are required to comply with the regulations under the Act in order to continue operations.\\r\\n\\r\\nSIM is also given the EduTrust award for having achieved satisfactory to commendable performance in key areas of management and the provision of educational services.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor more details, you can refer to the CPE website at https:\\/\\/www.ssg-wsg.gov.sg.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619347940,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619347940,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619347940),(33,16,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":16,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"How do I apply for SIM GE programme?\",\"answer\":\"Majority of the programme applications are to be submitted online. International students can only apply for full-time programme as per Immigration and Checkpoints Authority (ICA) requirements. SIM GE will provide assistance to submit Student\'s Pass application.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease refer to the website to apply for the specific programme you are interested in.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nLocal Applicants\\r\\nApplication fee must be made online with MasterCard\\/Visa Credit Card or eNETS. Other modes of payment are not accepted.\\r\\n\\r\\nAll original documents must be presented for verification at Blk A Level 2, Student Recruitment & Payment Office, SIM HQ 461 Clementi Road, Singapore 599491 within 7 days after submission or before closing date for application, whichever is earlier.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nInternational Applicants\\r\\nApplication fee must be made online with MasterCard\\/Visa Credit Card. Other modes of payment are not accepted. \\r\\n\\r\\nAfter payment, please proceed to complete the Student\'s Pass application.\\r\\n\\r\\nYou may submit your documents by the following options:\\r\\n1) Bring along the ORIGINAL documents for verification at SIM\\u2019s Student Recruitment Centre,\\r\\n    BLK A  Level 2 at SIM Headquarters, 461 Clementi Road, Singapore 599491\\r\\nOR\\r\\n2) Mail by courier the original notarized documents to:\\r\\n    Admissions Department (SIM GE)\\r\\n    SIM Headquarters\\r\\n    461 Clementi Road\\r\\n    Singapore 599491\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619347975,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619347975,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619347975),(34,17,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":17,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Can I apply to SIM GE with a Diploma\\/Advanced Diploma from private schools?\",\"answer\":\"Prospective students should have diploma from the local polytechnics in Singapore or SIM Diploma to meet the general admission requirements for an undergraduate programme. Selection of students is done by an Admissions Committee and is competitive. The final decision on admission rests with the respective universities. Students with Diploma\\/Advanced Diploma from private schools may apply and be considered on a case by case basis.  Other requirements such as IELTS\\/TOEFL may apply.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348155,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348155,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348155),(35,18,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":18,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Can my child \\/ I enrol in SIM with GCE \'N\' Level qualification?\",\"answer\":\"We do not have any programmes catered to students with GCE \'N\' Level qualification.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348254,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348254,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348254),(36,19,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":19,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Can I check the status of my application online?\",\"answer\":\"All applicants will be informed of their application outcome via email and SIMConnect applicant portal within one month of course commencement.  Verbal offers of admission will not be made nor accepted.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348337,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348337,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348337),(37,20,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":20,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"What are the available financial assistance schemes?\",\"answer\":\"You may obtain study loans from the following financial institutions:\\r\\n\\r\\nMaybank\\r\\nTel: 1800 629 2265\\r\\nWebsite: http:\\/\\/www.maybank2u.com.sg\\r\\n\\r\\nPOSB\\r\\nTel: 6333 0033\\r\\nWebsite: http:\\/\\/www.posb.com.sg\\r\\n\\r\\nRHB Bank Berhad\\r\\nTel: 1800 323 0100\\r\\nWebsite: http:\\/\\/www.rhbbank.com.sg\\r\\n\\r\\nCIMB Bank\\r\\nTel: 6333 7777\\r\\nWebsite: http:\\/\\/www.cimbbank.com.sg\\r\\n\\r\\nOCBC Bank\\r\\nTel: 1800 363 3333\\r\\nWebsite: http:\\/\\/www.frankbyocbc.com\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease contact the above institutions directly if you wish to obtain a loan.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nInterest-Free Instalment Plans\\r\\nWhen you charge above S$500 to your OCBC Visa\\/MasterCard, you can enjoy interest-free instalments of six or 12-months. Terms and conditions apply.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor more information, please call:\\r\\n\\r\\nOCBC\\r\\nTel: 1800 363 3333\\r\\nWebsite: http:\\/\\/www.ocbc.com.sg\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348428,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348428,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348428),(38,21,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":21,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"My application is unsuccessful. How can I appeal for admission?\",\"answer\":\"You may submit an appeal by writing in to us at study@sim.edu.sg with reasons and supporting documents (if any).\\r\\n\\r\\nSubmission of appeals should be done as soon as possible to allow Admissions sufficient time to consider your appeal.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348489,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348489,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348489),(39,22,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":22,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"How do I collect my Student\'s Pass?\",\"answer\":\"You must make an e-appointment with ICA before collecting your Student\'s Pass. Please refer to the instruction as stipulated on your In-Principle Approval letter.\\r\\n\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348546,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348546,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348546),(40,23,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":23,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"What is the duration of coverage for the fee protection scheme and medical insurance?\",\"answer\":\"The coverage applies to the entire duration of your studies in SIM.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348580,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348580,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348580),(41,24,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":24,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Does SIM offer job placements to students after their studies?\",\"answer\":\"Our Career Development Office helps students develop and identify career objectives through professional programmes that enhance self-awareness and career skills. We provide the following professional programmes to students:\\r\\n- Career workshops\\r\\n- Career guidance\\r\\n- Career events\\r\\n- Internship and job opportunities\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348675,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348675,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348675),(42,25,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":25,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Can I defer from the programme whilst in the midst of doing the programme?\",\"answer\":\"Students have to apply for leave of absence from the Student Services Centre.  Application will be subjected to the University\'s consideration and approval.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348737,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348737,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348737),(43,26,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":26,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Can I pursue a part-time programme while serving National Service (NS)?\\r\\n\",\"answer\":\"You may pursue a part-time programme while serving National Service (NS) if you are able to attend classes\\/lectures in the evenings and weekends.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348816,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348816,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348816),(44,27,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":27,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"I am in my final semester of my diploma, can I apply for the programme which is commencing in the coming intake?\",\"answer\":\"Yes, you may submit an application with all your completed semester results whilst attending your final semester.  However, you are required to submit your final semester results once it is available. \\r\\n\\r\\nPlease note that the above does not apply to all programmes.  For clarifications, please call our Recruitment Hotline at 6248 9746.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619348949,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619348949,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619348949),(45,28,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":28,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"What are the programmes available for GCE \'A\' level holders?\",\"answer\":\"Those with GCE \'A\' level qualification can choose programmes from the following awarding Universities \\/ Institutions:\\r\\n\\r\\nUniversity of London\\r\\nRMIT University\\r\\nUniversity of Wollongong\\r\\nUniversity at Buffalo, the State University of New York\\r\\n\\r\\nUniversity of Stirling\\r\\n\\r\\nSIM Global Education\\r\\nYou may refer to our website for the list of programmes offered and admission criteria.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619349005,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619349005,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619349005),(46,29,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":29,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Do I need to get a sponsor for my Student\'s Pass application?\",\"answer\":\"You do not have to get a sponsor. SIM will be your sponsor for Student\'s Pass.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619349042,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619349042,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619349042),(47,30,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":30,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Does SIM offer any scholarships?\",\"answer\":\"Yes, new international students with exemplary academic results may apply for the SIM Global Education (SIM GE) Scholarship when they enrol for the Diploma programmes awarded by SIM GE.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe also offer scholarships to outstanding local and international students to pursue bachelor\'s degree programmes at SIM GE.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619349137,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619349137,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619349137),(48,31,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":31,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"Will the application fee be refunded if my application is unsuccessful?\",\"answer\":\"Application fee is neither refundable nor transferable.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619349182,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619349182,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619349182),(49,32,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":32,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"How can I pay the application fee?\",\"answer\":\"Application fee must be made online with MasterCard\\/Visa Credit Card or eNETS. Other modes of payment are not accepted.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619349243,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619349243,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619349243),(50,33,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":33,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"How can I pay the application fee?\",\"answer\":\"SIM do not accept predicted or provisional results. Applicants must apply with their official results.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619349293,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619349293,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619349293),(51,34,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":34,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"I am not sure which programme I prefer. Can I apply for more than one programme?\",\"answer\":\"Yes, you can apply for as many programmes as you wish. However, for every application made, a separate application fee is applicable.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe exception is the degrees developed and awarded by the University at Buffalo, The State University of New York, where only one application is allowed.\\r\\n\\r\\nNote that while you can apply for more than one programme, you are allowed to pursue only one qualification-based programme at any one time.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619349354,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619349354,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619349354),(52,35,'common\\models\\Faq','faq','create','{\"id\":35,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"question\":\"How will I know if my Student\'s Pass application is successful?\",\"answer\":\"SIM will notify you via Mymail email once Immigration and Checkpoint Authority (ICA) releases your payment of Issuance fee notification.  After payment is made please download your  In-Principle Approval (IPA) letter.  Please follow all instructions on the letter carefully and look out for our email.\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619349389,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619349389,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619349389),(53,6,'common\\models\\Enquiries','enquiries','create','{\"id\":6,\"user_id\":21,\"school_id\":\"1\",\"enquiry\":\"When i graduate, do i need to go Australia to attend my graduation ceremony? \\n\",\"notes\":null,\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619367439,\"created_by\":21,\"updated_at\":1619367439,\"updated_by\":21}',21,1619367439),(54,5,'common\\models\\EventsRegistration','events-registration','delete','{\"id\":5,\"event_id\":2,\"notes\":null,\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1617889245,\"created_by\":21,\"updated_at\":1617889245,\"updated_by\"