es of the programme may obtain junior management and supervisory positions with air services providers, airlines and airport organisations located throughout the world\",\"programme_structure\":\"Teaching Faculty\\r\\nLecturers are both academic and industry-based professionals with extensive work experience and knowledge in their domain\\r\\n\\r\\nDelivery Mode\\r\\nThe course is 100% face-to-face lecture-based learning. Coursework includes attendance at lectures, discussions of case studies, tests, presentations, and completion of group and individually-written assignments\\r\\n\\r\\nCurriculum\\r\\n12-month part-time programme of 8 modules:\\r\\n\\r\\nPrinciples and Practices in Aviation\\r\\nPrinciples and Skills of Management\\r\\nOperations Management\\r\\nAccounting and Finance in the Aviation Industry\\r\\nBusiness Analytics Concepts and Applications\\r\\nEmerging Technologies and Innovations\\r\\nDesign Thinking for Innovation\\r\\nAviation Industry Project\\r\\nContact hours: 30 hrs per module, total: 240 hrs\\r\\n\\r\\nDuration of each lesson is 7.5 hour, lectures at least one full-day a week\\r\\n\\r\\nClick here for the module outline\\r\\n\\r\\nCandidature Period\\r\\nMaximum allowed period to complete the 12-month programme is 24 months\\r\\n\\r\\nNo refund or recourse should the student fail to complete in the maximum period\\r\\n\\r\\nSIM reserves the right to recommend and withdraw a student who cannot cope with the demands of the programme\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum Class Size\\r\\nMinimum class size to commence: 25 students\\r\\n\\r\\nIf take-up rate does not meet the minimum to commence, students will be informed within one month before class commences\",\"admission_criteria\":\"Admission Criteria\\r\\nPolytechnic Diploma or equivalent\\r\\nEnglish Language Requirements\\r\\nGCE \\u2018O\\u2019 level credit pass (grade 1 to 6) in English (as a first language) or equivalent\",\"fees\":\"Course Fee\\r\\nTotal: S$6,000 + prevailing GST (for 2020 Intakes)\\r\\n\\r\\nApplication Fee applies\",\"exemptions\":\"Exemption Eligibility\\r\\nNil\",\"profiles\":\"Academic Profiles \\r\\nLecturers\\u2019 List \\u2013 SDAM\\r\\n\\r\\nAverage teacher-student ratio 1:60\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum class size : 25\\r\\n\\r\\nMaximum class size : 100\",\"assessments_exams\":\"Assessment & Exams\\r\\nContinuous assessment and end-of-module test\\r\\n\\r\\nContinuous assessments include case studies, class \\/ online tests, discussions, presentations, group and individual assignments\\r\\n\\r\\nTo attain a pass for module with grading, students must achieve an overall minimum Grade Point Average (GPA) of 1.0 (grade \\u2018D\\u2019) for that module\\r\\n\\r\\nAttendance requirement\\r\\nAttendance requirement: 75%\\r\\n\\r\\nGraduation\\r\\nGraduating students who passed all 8 modules will be issued a transcript and awarded with a Specialist Diploma in Aviation Management from SIM upon graduation\",\"entry_qualification\":\"[\\\"diploma\\\",\\\"a-level\\\"]\",\"application\":\"Application\\r\\nNot Applicable\",\"course_start_end_date\":\"Intake Month(s)\\r\\nPart-time: Jan, Jul\\r\\nFor more information on the programme, please contact David Khoe (davidkhoe@sim.edu.sg) or Ismayawaty (ismayawaty@sim.edu.sg)\",\"scholarships_award\":\"Scholarships and Award\",\"overview\":\"Overview\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/11\\/SIM1.jpg\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616638690,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619700363,\"updated_by\":2}',2,1619700363),(68,20,'common\\models\\Courses','courses','create','{\"id\":20,\"school_id\":4,\"name\":\"Diploma in Accounting\",\"mode_of_study\":\"full_time\",\"disciplines\":\"Accounting\",\"sub_disciplines\":\"Nil\",\"academic_level\":\"Diploma\",\"introduction\":\"Laying strong foundation in accounting\\r\\nYou acquire:\\r\\n\\r\\nGood foundation in accounting concepts and practice\\r\\nAccreditation towards professional accounting qualification.\\r\\nFurther Education\\r\\nWith the Diploma, you can apply for advanced standing to the various degree programmes with our partner universities.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease click here for details on the advanced standing.\\r\\n\\r\\nProfessional Accounting Qualification\\r\\nObtain credit exemptions from:\\r\\nInstitute of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales (ICAEW) ICAEW \\u2013 https:\\/\\/www.icaew.com\\/en\\r\\n\\r\\nChartered Institute of Management Accountants (CIMA) CIMA \\u2013 https:\\/\\/www.cimaglobal.com\\/\\r\\n\\r\\nAssociation of Chartered Certified Accountants (ACCA) \\u2013 https:\\/\\/www.accaglobal.com\\/sg\\/en.html\\r\\n\\r\\nCareer Prospects\\r\\nAccounting and finance-related positions in:\\r\\n\\r\\nFinancial services\\r\\nAuditing services\\r\\nBanking\\r\\nBusiness development\\r\\nInvestment management\\r\\nMarketing and retail\\r\\nManufacturing\\r\\nPublic service\",\"programme_structure\":\"Teaching Faculty\\r\\nLecturers are both academic and industry-based professionals with extensive work experience and knowledge in their domain.\\r\\n\\r\\nDelivery Mode\\r\\nThe course is 100% face-to-face lecture-based learning. Coursework includes attendance at lectures, discussions of case studies, tests, presentations, and completion of group and individually-written assignments.\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Support\\r\\nClasses and workshops are available on study skills, academic writing and presentation.\\r\\n\\r\\nAcademic Materials\\r\\nInclude module outlines, reading lists and handbooks on study strategies\\r\\n\\r\\nCurriculum\\r\\n15-month full-time programme (5 terms) of 15 modules:\\r\\n\\r\\nAuditing and Assurance\\r\\nBusiness Accounting\\r\\nBusiness Management and Communications\\r\\nBusiness Mathematics\\r\\nBusiness Statistics\\r\\nBusiness Law\\r\\nCompany Law and Secretarial Practice\\r\\nCost and Management Accounting\\r\\nEconomics for Managers\\r\\nFinancial Accounting and Reporting\\r\\nInformation Systems for Business\\r\\nManaging Human Resources\\r\\nManaging Business Finance\\r\\nPrinciples of Marketing\\r\\nTaxation\\r\\nContact hours: 42 hrs per module, total: 630 hrs\\r\\n\\r\\n5 terms. Each term is a period of three months.\\r\\n\\r\\nLectures at least 6 times a week (Mon-Sat)\\r\\n\\r\\nEach lesson: 3 hrs\\r\\n\\r\\nClick here for the programme schedule\\r\\n\\r\\nClick here for the module outline\\r\\n\\r\\nProgramme Calendar\\r\\n2 intakes a year in April & October, each covering 15 months.\\r\\n\\r\\nApril intake: early April to end-June (following year)\\r\\n\\r\\nOctober intake: early October to end-December (following year)\\r\\n\\r\\nCandidature Period\\r\\nMaximum allowed period to complete the 15-month programme is 30 months or 2.5 years.\\r\\n\\r\\nNo refund or recourse when student did not complete in the maximum period.\\r\\n\\r\\nSIM reserves the right to recommend and withdraw a student who cannot cope with the demands of the programme, especially when the student\\u2019s pass has expired.\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum Class Size\\r\\nMinimum class size to commence: 25 students. Students will be informed within 30 days before class commences.\",\"admission_criteria\":\"Admission Criteria\\r\\nGCE A-level, IB diploma, or other equivalent pre-university certifications, or Polytechnic diploma or SIM GE\\u2019s foundation programme, namely, Management Foundation Studies (MFS)\\r\\nOther qualifications will be assessed based on the equivalence to GCE \\u2018A\\u2019 level examinations.\\r\\nApplicants who do not meet the academic requirements might be recommended to undergo a 6-month Management Foundation Studies (MFS) programme. Click here for details of the MFS programme.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor international applicants (full-time programme only)\\r\\nInternational applicants will be assessed on the qualification\\u2019s equivalent to the GCE \\u2018A\\u2019 level examinations.\\r\\n\\r\\nRefer to the details on qualifications listed in the International Student Pros