5s programmes with top ranking and reputable universities from Australia, Europe, the United Kingdom and the United States. Its current enrolment stands at about 17,000 full and part-time students and adult learners from over 40 countries with about 23% full-time international students. SIM GE\\u00d5s holistic learning approach and culturally diverse learning environment aim to equip students with an all-rounded global education. Besides building competencies and skills needed to thrive in the real world, SIM GE also hones the soft skills of students through a wide range of student life, career development and networking activities.\",\"continent\":\"singapore\",\"highlights\":\"Nil\",\"certifications\":\"13 available programmes\\r\\nFull-time:\\r\\nDiploma In Accounting\\r\\nDiploma in Banking and Finance\\r\\nDiploma in International Business\\r\\nDiploma in Management Studies\\r\\nInformation Technology Foundation Studies\\r\\nManagement Foundation Studies\\r\\nManagement Foundation Studies - Blended(Only for Singaporean & PR).\\r\\n\\r\\nPart-time\\r\\nSpecialist Diploma In Aviation Management\\r\\nGraduate Diploma in Human Resource Management\\r\\nGraduate Certificate in Business Analytics\\r\\nGraduate Diploma in Business Analytics\\r\\nGraduate Diploma in Digital Marketing\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/SIMGE-transparent-logo.png\",\"tags\":\"[\\\"sim\\\"]\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616638690,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619845975,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619845975),(121,5,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":5,\"name\":\"University of London (UOL)\",\"description\":\"The University of London is one of the largest, most diverse universities in the UK with over 120,000 students in London, and a further 50,000 studying across 190 countries. Academic direction of programmes offered at SIM is provided by Goldsmiths, London School of Economics and Political Science and University College London.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe recently welcomed the 35th intake of the LSE-led programmes. In fact, SIM will celebrate the 35th anniversary of the collaboration with UOL in 2021. The repertoire of programmes has grown to now include Accounting, Banking, Business Analytics, Data Science, Digital Innovation, Economics, Finance, International Relations, Politics, Management, IT and Computing.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn 2020, classes commenced for new programmes with Goldsmiths\' Department of Computing. The BSc programmes in Computer Science, Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence, Web and Mobile Development saw enrolment grow ten-fold from semester one to semester two! We also started a suite of postgraduate programmes in Data Science, AI and FinTech led by Goldsmiths.\",\"continent\":\"uk\",\"highlights\":\"LSE is first in Europe for Social Sciences and Management in the 2020 QS World University Rankings.\\r\\n\\r\\nUCL is 10th in the 2021 QS World University Rankings\\r\\n\\r\\nGoldsmiths is top 25 in the UK for the quality of research in the Research Excellence Framework 2014-2021\",\"certifications\":\"29 available programmes.\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time and Part-Time:\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) in Accounting and Finance\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) in Banking and Finance\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) In Business and Management\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time:\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) in Computer Science\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) in Computer Science (Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence)\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) in Computer Science (Web and Mobile Development)\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) in Data Science and Business Analytics\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) in Economics\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/UOL-logo.png\",\"tags\":\"[\\\"uol\\\"]\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616638690,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619846000,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846000),(122,6,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":6,\"name\":\"University at Buffalo, The State University of New York\",\"description\":\"Founded in 1846, the University at Buffalo (UB), The State University of New York (SUNY), is one of the leading public research universities in the U.S.  Within the 64-campus SUNY system, UB is the flagship campus.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor the seventh consecutive year, UB is ranked among the nation\\u00d5s Top 50 Public Universities, coming in at No. 34. UB also ranks No. 88 among Best National Universities, public and private, according to U.S. News.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe rankings are based on an assessment of more than 1,900 of the country\\u00d5s four-year colleges and universities, in addition to data reported to the U.S. Department of Education.\\r\\n\\r\\nUB is among a number of public universities that are members of the prestigious Association of American Universities (AAU) included in the ranking. Other AAU public universities ranked by U.S. News for 2020 include University of California, Berkeley; University of Michigan; The Ohio State University; Indiana University Bloomington; Michigan State; Penn State; University of Wisconsin-Madison; University of North Carolina, Chapel Hill; Purdue; and Rutgers.\\r\\n\\r\\nAccreditations\\r\\nUB is accredited by the following associations:\\r\\n\\r\\nMiddle States Commission on Higher Education\\r\\nNew York State Board of Regents\\r\\nThe university is a member of the following associations:\\r\\n\\r\\nAmerican Council on Education\\r\\nAssociation of American Colleges and Universities\\r\\nAssociation of American Universities\\r\\nAssociation of Colleges and Universities of the State of New York\\r\\nNational Association of State Universities and Land-Grant Colleges\\r\\nIn addition, the School of Management is accredited by AACSB International \\u00d0 The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business. UB\\u00d5s Bachelor programmes at SIM GE include Communication, Psychology, Economics, International Trade, Sociology, and Business Administration. \",\"continent\":\"us\",\"highlights\":\"High quality and interactive American education\\r\\nStudents admitted are regular UB students (no distinction between Singapore and Buffalo)\\r\\nAdmission standards and academic expectations are the same as UB\\r\\nAccreditation and recognition of UB degrees\\r\\nQuality assurance mechanisms\\r\\nOptions to study one semester in Buffalo\\u00d5s home campus in US\\r\\nFull-time Resident Director and Assistant Resident Director\\r\\nFull-time Academic Advisors\\r\\nFull-time, regular UB faculty and visiting faculty teach in the program covering the full semester\\r\\nExcellent value with lower tuition costs here than studying in the US\\r\\nSuccessful graduates and extensive alumni network\",\"certifications\":\"28 Certifications\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/univeristy-of-buffalo-logo.png\",\"tags\":\"[\\\"ub\\\"]\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616638690,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619846027,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846027),(123,7,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":7,\"name\":\"Monash College\",\"description\":\"For over 25 years, Monash College has been helping international students get into their desired degree courses and preparing them for success in the workforce. Monash College is 100 per cent owned by Monash University, a world top 100 ranked university^, and Australia\\u2019s largest university. Successful completion of a Monash College program offers an international student guaranteed entry to a range of degrees at Monash University*.\\r\\n\\r\\n*Entry requirements into Monash University apply. Please visit monashcollege.edu.au for details.\\r\\n^QS World University rankings 2020\",\"continent\":\"australia\",\"highlights\":\" Monash University Rankings\\r\\n\\r\\n45th globally in the National Taiwan University (NTU) Ranking 2020.\\r\\n64th globally in the Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2021.\\r\\n73rd globally and third in Australia in ShanghaiRanking\\u2019s Academic Ranking of World Universities 2019.\\r\\n21st in the World\\u2019s Most International Universities in 2017 as released by Times Higher Education.\\r\\n55th globally according to the Quacquarelli Symonds (QS) World University Rankings 2021.\\r\\nRanked sixth in the world in the Times Higher Education Golden Age university ranking 2020.\",\"certifications\":\"1 available certification as below.\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time\\r\\nMonash University Foundation Year\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/10\\/MonashCollege-200x80px-1.png\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616726629,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619846094,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846094),(124,8,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":8,\"name\":\"The University of Sydney\",\"description\":\"The University of Sydney, Australia\\u2019s first university, has an international reputation for outstanding teaching, as a centre of research excellence and as an active and engaged community leader. University of Sydney students and researchers come from all over the world and all backgrounds to prepare for a life of challenge and change.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe University of Sydney graduates are found across the globe. We constantly build on the innovations of our alumni, who include prime ministers, Nobel laureates, Oscar winners, business leaders, medical pioneers, artists, intellectuals and activists.\",\"continent\":\"australia\",\"highlights\":\"The University of Sydney is Australia\\u2019s first university, founded in 1850.\\r\\n\\r\\nRanked 2nd in Australia and 15th in the world for University nursing education and research excellence (QS World University Rankings by Subject 2019)\\r\\nRanked 1st in Australia and 5th in the world for Graduate Employability (QS Graduate Employability Rankings 2019)\\r\\nA member of the Group of Eight (Australia\\u2019s prestigious research-intensive universities)\\r\\n25 years of partnership with SIM GE in education of healthcare professionals\",\"certifications\":\"2 available certifications as below\\r\\n\\r\\nPart-Time\\r\\nBachelor of Nursing (Honours)\\r\\nBachelor of Nursing (Post-Registration)\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/the-university-of-sydney-logo.png\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616726696,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619846143,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846143),(125,10,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":10,\"name\":\"La Trobe University\",\"description\":\"La Trobe University was founded in 1967 as Victoria\\u2019s third university and have equipped more than 190,000 graduates with skills and experience to build successful careers. Among their graduates are CEOs of prominent organisations, parliamentarians, human rights activists, researchers and Olympians. La Trobe has also built a reputation as an international university, welcoming students from across the globe. They have grown to host more than 36,000 students with over 8 000 international students from 110 countries.\\r\\n\\r\\nLa Trobe University has six campuses spread out across the state of Victoria with their largest campus situated in Melbourne, the capital city of Victoria, Australia.\\r\\n\\r\\nMore on La Trobe University \\u2013 https:\\/\\/www.latrobe.edu.au\\/\\r\\nMore on La Trobe University\\u2019s Ranking \\u2013 https:\\/\\/www.latrobe.edu.au\\/about\\/rankings-and-ratings\",\"continent\":\"australia\",\"highlights\":\"Internationally recognised for research, with areas of research rated at, above or well above world standard (Excellence in Research for Australia Report 2018)\\r\\nRanked in the top 45 universities for Hospitality and Tourism Management (Shanghai Ranking\\u2019s Global Ranking of Academic Subjects 2019)\\r\\nRanked 52nd globally in the Times Higher Education Golden Age Rankings 2019\\r\\nRanked in the world\\u2019s top 400 universities by all three major independent ranking agencies (Academic Ranking of World Universities 2019; QS World University Rankings 2020; Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2019)\\r\\nRanked 14th in Australia and 4th in Victoria (QS Graduate Employability Rankings 2019)\\r\\nMember of the Council of Australasian University Tourism and Hospitality Education (CAUTHE)\\r\\nLa Trobe Business School is an accredited member of AACSB \\u2013 the Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business\",\"certifications\":\"Two available certifications as below.\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-time\\r\\nBachelor of Business (Event Management)(Top-up)\\r\\nBachelor of Business (Tourism and Hospitality)\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2020\\/09\\/LTU_Int_H_RGB_V3-200x76px.png\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616765859,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619846182,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846182),(126,11,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":11,\"name\":\"University of Manchester\",\"description\":\"With a distinguished history of academic achievement and an ambitious agenda for the future, The University of Manchester offers you a superb learning experience, rooted in a rich heritage and boosted by cutting-edge research and innovation.\\r\\n\\r\\nPart of the prestigious Russell Group of universities, Manchester has much to offer you. The University is highly respected among academic and business communities \\u2013 a reputation that its graduates also enjoy.\\r\\n\\r\\nOur tradition of success in learning and research stretches back over 180 years, encompassing the birth of the modern computer, splitting of the atom and the founding principles of modern economics. Many more world- changing innovations have their roots here, at The University of Manchester. Rated 5th in the UK in terms of \\u2018research power\\u2019 in the 2014 Research Excellence Framework, we enjoy a global reputation for our pioneering research, which enhances our problem-based approach to undergraduate learning.\\r\\n\\r\\nWebsite: www.manchester.ac.uk\",\"continent\":\"uk\",\"highlights\":\"Alliance Manchester Business School is accredited by all three major bodies i.e. Triple Crown Accreditation \\u2013 The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business (AACSB International), Association of MBAs (AMBA) and European Quality Improvement System (EQUIS)\\r\\nThe University of Manchester has 25 Nobel Prize winners amongst its current and former staff and students\\r\\nThe University is ranked 6th in the UK and 34th in the world by Shanghai Jiao Tong Academic Ranking of World Universities 2018\\r\\nLargest global alumni community of any campus-based university in the UK, with 380,000 graduates in more than 190 countries\\r\\nAlliance Manchester Business School is one of the country\\u2019s major schools for business and management research, ranked 2nd in the UK in terms of \\u2018research power\\u2019 according to the 2014 Research Excellence Framework.\\r\\nAlliance Manchester Business School is ranked 4th in the UK, 10th in Europe and 36th in the world by Financial Times Global MBA Ranking 2018\\r\\nThe University is ranked as the number one most targeted university by the UK\\u2019s leading graduate employers in 2017-2018 (The Graduate Market in 2018, High Fliers Research)\",\"certifications\":\"Not available programmes\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/02\\/sim000754.png\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616766133,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619846210,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846210),(127,12,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":12,\"name\":\"University of Warwick\",\"description\":\"Established in 1965, the University of Warwick is one of the UK\\u2019s leading research universities, with an acknowledged reputation for excellence in research and teaching, for innovation and for links with business and industry. Warwick has consistently maintained its position in the top 10 of UK league tables , offering courses with high academic content that are stimulating and challenging.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhy choose the University of Warwick?\\r\\n\\r\\nRanked 62nd in QS World University Rankings 2020\\r\\nA member of the prestigious Russell Group of UK universities\\r\\nTop 10 of UK league tables (The Complete University Guide 2019\\/The Guardian University League Table 2020)\\r\\nRanked as the third-most targeted university among the UK\\u2019s top graduate employers in 2017-2018 (Graduate Market Survey 2018, High Fliers Research)\\r\\nWMG is one of the world\\u2019s leading research and education groups, with a track record of hugely successful industry collaboration\\r\\nAbout WMG\\r\\nWMG is one of UK\\u2019s leading academic manufacturing team with exceptionally strong links to companies world-wide and a part of the University of Warwick. WMG provides training to over 2,200 postgraduates in the UK and through centres in China, Thailand, Cyprus, Turkey, Malaysia and Singapore.\\r\\n\\r\\nWMG has pioneered an international model for working with industry, commerce and public sectors. The Group\\u2019s strength is to provide companies with the opportunity to gain a competitive edge by understanding a company\\u2019s strategy and working in partnership with them to find innovative solutions through multi-disciplinary research. WMG\\u2019s research teams comprise a range of specialists including engineers, physical scientists, material scientists, mathematicians, designers, IT specialists, social scientists, economists and knowledge transfer experts.\\r\\n\\r\\nToday WMG work across many sectors including automotive; aerospace and defence; energy and utilities; food and drink; healthcare and pharmaceutical; security; and rail. The strength of its expertise spans across five key themes: design; materials; manufacturing; systems; and business transformation.\\r\\n\\r\\nIts success over the past 37 years is the result of cutting edge research and effective knowledge transfer, working with global companies such as Jaguar Land Rover, TATA, TVS, BAE Systems, AstraZeneca, Siemens, GlaxoSmithKline and Airbus to name but a few.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Group occupies a unique position between academia and industry; all of its research projects are dedicated to finding solutions to real world problems, and participants benefit from its first-hand understanding of the issues facing modern industry.\",\"continent\":\"uk\",\"highlights\":\"Programme Highlights\\r\\nThree-way participation: University + Organisation + Participant\\r\\nCombine academic excellence with industrial experience\\r\\nDeveloped with industry to address real world problems\\r\\nFirst-hand understanding of issues facing modern business and industry\\r\\nApplication-based assignments and projects\\r\\nGlobal experience and inputs\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nBenefits to Businesses\\r\\nOn the job (in-company) assignments & projects\\r\\nApproach business issue as you would with an external consultant\\r\\nImmediate application of both concepts and tools\\r\\n\",\"certifications\":\"8 available programmes\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time and Part-Time\\r\\nMaster of Science in Cyber Security and Management\\r\\nMaster of Science in Engineering Business Management\\r\\nMaster of Science in Programme and Project Management\\r\\nMaster Science in Supply Chain & Logistics Management\\r\\n\\r\\nPart-Time\\r\\nPostgraduate Award in Cyber Security and Management\\r\\nPostgraduate Award in Engineering Business Management\\r\\nPostgraduate Award in Programme and Project Management\\r\\nPostgraduate Award in Supply Chin and Logistics Management\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/WMG-logo.png\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616766417,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619846291,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846291),(128,13,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":13,\"name\":\"University of Birmingham\",\"description\":\"The University of Birmingham (Birmingham) was founded in 1900 and is now one of the largest in the UK, offering degrees across a wide range of disciplines. It is a major centre of research and academic study with an established international reputation for excellence with 11 Nobel Prize winners among its staff and alumni.\\r\\n\\r\\nBirmingham has been challenging and developing great minds for more than a century. Characterised by a tradition of innovation, research at the University has broken new ground, pushed forward the boundaries of knowledge and made an impact on people\\u2019s lives.\\r\\n\\r\\nBirmingham is constantly developing and evolving to become a leading global university. This is being achieved through the University\\u2019s enhanced research power and reach; the breadth and depth of academic portfolio; the extent of global networks and the distinctiveness of exceptional student experience.\\r\\n\\r\\nGraduate Employability\\r\\nSecond most frequently targeted university among UK\\u2019s top employers (The Graduate Market in 2020, High Fliers Research)\\r\\n\\r\\nwww.birmingham.ac.uk\",\"continent\":\"uk\",\"highlights\":\"Ranked 87th in the world (QS World University Rankings 2021)\\r\\nRanked 16th in the UK by the Guardian University Guide 2020\\r\\nTop 13 in the UK University League Table (The Complete University Guide 2021)\\r\\nA member of the prestigious Russell Group of 24 UK research-intensive universities\\r\\nA member of the Universitas 21 global network of top universities around the world\\r\\nA gold-rated university for outstanding teaching and learning in the UK (Teaching Excellence Framework 2017 \\u2013 2020)\",\"certifications\":\"13 available Programmes\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-time and Part-Time:\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) Business Management (Top-up)\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time: \\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours) Accounting and Finance (Top-up)\\r\\nBachelor of Science (Honours)  Business Management with Communications and Year in Industry (Top-up)\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/programmes\\/programme-listing\\/?finder_university=university-of-birmingham\",\"tags\":\"[\\\"uob\\\"]\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616767291,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619846321,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846321),(129,14,'common\\models\\UniversityPartners','university-partners','update','{\"id\":14,\"name\":\"University of Stirling\",\"description\":\"The University of Stirling has been crowned the UK\\u2019s Sports University of the Year in recognition of its world-class facilities and excellence across sports performance, research and education. \\r\\n\\r\\nFounded by Royal Charter in 1967, the University of Stirling was the first genuinely new university in Scotland for over 400 years.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe results of the University\\u2019s performance in the 2014 Research Excellence Framework (REF) positioned Stirling as one of the top research-led universities in the UK with almost three quarters of research activity rated either world-leading or internationally excellent. Stirling is ranked 6th in Scotland and 45th in the UK, with our Management School ranked in the UK top 25 for Business and Management.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn learning and teaching, the University is committed to delivering high quality programmes that produce intellectually able graduates who are highly sought after by employers. We are ambitious for our students, and our flexible learning opportunities enable them to explore and discover new subjects and interests.\",\"continent\":\"uk\",\"highlights\":\"The University of Stirling regularly performs well in the various newspaper surveys of higher education. Here are some of the accolades:\\r\\n\\r\\nA 5-star ranking for teaching, employability, internationalisation, facilities and inclusiveness in the QS World University Rankings 2020\\r\\nSports University of the Year (The Times and The Sunday Times Good University Guide 2020)\\r\\nMarketing \\u2013 Top 2 in Scotland, Top 10 in the UK (The Complete University Guide 2020)\\r\\nSports Science \\u2013 Top 5 in Scotland, Top 20 in the UK (The Complete University Guide 2020)\\r\\nHome to the Institute for Retail Studies, an acknowledged centre of excellence for retailing\\r\\nStirling is Scotland\\u2019s University for Sporting Excellence, and ranked top 20 in the UK for Sports Science (The Complete University Guide 2020)\",\"certifications\":\"5 available programmes as below\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time and Part-Time\\r\\nBachelor of Arts (Honours) Events Management\\r\\nBachelor of Arts (Honours) Marketing\\r\\nBachelor of Arts (Honours) Retail Marketing\\r\\nBachelor of Arts (Honours) Sports Studies and Marketing.\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-Time\\r\\nBachelor of Arts (Honours) Digital Media Top-up\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/sim000875-2.png\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616767757,\"created_by\":1,\"updated_at\":1619846358,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846358),(130,6,'common\\models\\Courses','courses','update','{\"id\":6,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"name\":\"Specialist Diploma in Aviation Management\",\"mode_of_study\":\"full_time\",\"disciplines\":\"Specialist\",\"sub_disciplines\":\"Aviation\",\"academic_level\":\"Diploma\",\"introduction\":\"Opportunities in the Aviation Industry\\r\\nThe aviation industry in Singapore is well-placed to benefit from the growth potential of aviation-related activities. As an endeavour towards the drive to prepare the Singapore workforce the future economy, SIM GE has launched a Specialist Diploma in Aviation Management (SDAM) to hone the future skills of new talents in the aviation industry\\r\\n\\r\\nFurther Education\\r\\nGraduates are eligible for consideration for admission into the undergraduate degree in Aviation at SIM RMIT as well as undergraduate programmes in many other institutions\\r\\n\\r\\nCareer Prospects\\r\\nGraduates of the programme may obtain junior management and supervisory positions with air services providers, airlines and airport organisations located throughout the world\",\"programme_structure\":\"Teaching Faculty\\r\\nLecturers are both academic and industry-based professionals with extensive work experience and knowledge in their domain\\r\\n\\r\\nDelivery Mode\\r\\nThe course is 100% face-to-face lecture-based learning. Coursework includes attendance at lectures, discussions of case studies, tests, presentations, and completion of group and individually-written assignments\\r\\n\\r\\nCurriculum\\r\\n12-month part-time programme of 8 modules:\\r\\n\\r\\nPrinciples and Practices in Aviation\\r\\nPrinciples and Skills of Management\\r\\nOperations Management\\r\\nAccounting and Finance in the Aviation Industry\\r\\nBusiness Analytics Concepts and Applications\\r\\nEmerging Technologies and Innovations\\r\\nDesign Thinking for Innovation\\r\\nAviation Industry Project\\r\\nContact hours: 30 hrs per module, total: 240 hrs\\r\\n\\r\\nDuration of each lesson is 7.5 hour, lectures at least one full-day a week\\r\\n\\r\\nClick here for the module outline\\r\\n\\r\\nCandidature Period\\r\\nMaximum allowed period to complete the 12-month programme is 24 months\\r\\n\\r\\nNo refund or recourse should the student fail to complete in the maximum period\\r\\n\\r\\nSIM reserves the right to recommend and withdraw a student who cannot cope with the demands of the programme\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum Class Size\\r\\nMinimum class size to commence: 25 students\\r\\n\\r\\nIf take-up rate does not meet the minimum to commence, students will be informed within one month before class commences\",\"admission_criteria\":\"Admission Criteria\\r\\nPolytechnic Diploma or equivalent\\r\\nEnglish Language Requirements\\r\\nGCE \\u2018O\\u2019 level credit pass (grade 1 to 6) in English (as a first language) or equivalent\",\"fees\":\"Course Fee\\r\\nTotal: S$6,000 + prevailing GST (for 2020 Intakes)\\r\\n\\r\\nApplication Fee applies\",\"exemptions\":\"Exemption Eligibility\\r\\nNil\",\"profiles\":\"Academic Profiles \\r\\nLecturers\\u2019 List \\u2013 SDAM\\r\\n\\r\\nAverage teacher-student ratio 1:60\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum class size : 25\\r\\n\\r\\nMaximum class size : 100\",\"assessments_exams\":\"Assessment & Exams\\r\\nContinuous assessment and end-of-module test\\r\\n\\r\\nContinuous assessments include case studies, class \\/ online tests, discussions, presentations, group and individual assignments\\r\\n\\r\\nTo attain a pass for module with grading, students must achieve an overall minimum Grade Point Average (GPA) of 1.0 (grade \\u2018D\\u2019) for that module\\r\\n\\r\\nAttendance requirement\\r\\nAttendance requirement: 75%\\r\\n\\r\\nGraduation\\r\\nGraduating students who passed all 8 modules will be issued a transcript and awarded with a Specialist Diploma in Aviation Management from SIM upon graduation\",\"entry_qualification\":\"[\\\"diploma\\\",\\\"a-level\\\"]\",\"application\":\"Application\\r\\nNot Applicable\",\"course_start_end_date\":\"Intake Month(s)\\r\\nPart-time: Jan, Jul\\r\\nFor more information on the programme, please contact David Khoe (davidkhoe@sim.edu.sg) or Ismayawaty (ismayawaty@sim.edu.sg)\",\"scholarships_award\":\"Scholarships and Award\",\"overview\":\"Overview\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/sim007217.jpg\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616638690,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619846497,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846497),(131,10,'common\\models\\Courses','courses','update','{\"id\":10,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"name\":\"Information Technology Foundation Studies\",\"mode_of_study\":\"full_time\",\"disciplines\":\"IT and Computer Science\",\"sub_disciplines\":\"Information Technology\",\"academic_level\":\"Certificate\",\"introduction\":\"Equip with the necessary foundation skills and knowledge in Information Technology \\r\\nThe programme is designed to provide appropriate foundation for students who wish to progress to study information technology at the diploma level\\r\\n\\r\\nFurther Education\\r\\nWith the Certificate, you can progress to Diploma in Information Technology\",\"programme_structure\":\"Teaching Faculty\\r\\nLecturers are both academic and industry-based professionals with extensive work experience and expertise in their domain knowledge.\\r\\n\\r\\nDelivery Mode\\r\\nThe course is 100% face-to-face lecture-based learning. Coursework includes attendance at lectures, practical assessment, tests, presentations, and completion of group and individual-written assignments.\\r\\n\\r\\nStudents are required to access relevant Web sites and the Internet for research and assignments in their own time. Besides attending lectures, students also participate in computer lab sessions.\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Support\\r\\nClasses and workshops are organised to teach study skills, academic writing and presentation.\\r\\n\\r\\nAcademic Materials\\r\\nVirtual Learning Environment\\r\\nAcademic materials such as module books (soft copies), past assessment papers, reading lists and handbooks on good study strategies\\r\\nCurriculum\\r\\nIntroduction to Information Technology 1\\r\\nIntroduction to Information Technology 2\\r\\nMathematics and Statistics\\r\\nStudy Skills for Effective Learning\\r\\nWeb Programming Fundamentals\\r\\nPlease click here for the module outline.\\r\\n\\r\\nContact hours: 39 hours per module, total: 195 hours. Each lesson: 3 hours.\\r\\n\\r\\nProgramme Calendar\\r\\nFour intakes a year, each covering 6 months.  Please click here for the calendar.\\r\\n\\r\\nJanuary intake (early Jan to end-Jun)\\r\\nApril intake (early Apr to end-Sep)\\r\\nJuly intake (early Jul to end-Dec)\\r\\nOctober intake (early Oct to end-Mar)\\r\\nCandidature Period \\r\\nMaximum allowed period to complete the 6-month programme is 12 months or 1 year.\\r\\n\\r\\nStudents may re-apply for the programme if they did not complete the course in the maximum allowed period.\\r\\n\\r\\nNo refund or recourse should the student fail to complete in the maximum period.\\r\\n\\r\\nSIM has the right to withdraw a student who cannot cope with the demands of the programme, especially when the student\\u2019s pass has expired.\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum Class Size \\r\\nMinimum class size to commence: 35 students. Students will be informed within 30 days before class commences.\",\"admission_criteria\":\"Entry Requirements\\r\\nAt least 3 GCE \\u2018O\\u2019 level credit passes (Grade 1 to 6); or\\r\\n\\r\\nNitec Certificate (Minimum GPA 3.5) in:\\r\\n1. Communication Technology; or\\r\\n2. Digital Animation; or\\r\\n3. Digital Audio and Video Production; or\\r\\n4. Digital Media Design \\/ Digital Media Design (Interactive Media); or\\r\\n5. Digital Media Design (Digital Video Effects); or\\r\\n6. Info-Communications Technology (Cloud Computing); or\\r\\n7. Info-Communications Technology; or\\r\\n8. Info-Communications Technology (Mobile Networks & Applications) \\/ (Mobile Systems & Services); or\\r\\n9. Security Technology; or\\r\\n10. Info-Communications Technology (Networking & Systems Administration); or\\r\\n\\r\\nHigher Nitec Certificate; or\\r\\n\\r\\nOther qualifications will be assessed based on the equivalence to GCE \\u2018O\\u2019 level examinations.\\r\\n\\r\\nInternational Applicants (full-time)\\r\\nInternational applicants will be assessed on the qualification\\u2019s equivalent to the GCE \\u2018O\\u2019 level examinations.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease refer to the details on qualifications listed in the International Student Prospectus. Alternatively, you may click here for the list of overseas qualifications\\r\\n\\r\\nEnglish Language Requirement \\r\\nGCE \\u2018O\\u2019 level credit pass (Grade 1 to 6) in English (as a first language); or\\r\\nIELTS with an overall score of at least 5.5; or\\r\\nTOEFL score of at least 550 (paper-based) plus 4 in the Test of Written English (TWE); or\\r\\nSAT1 score of at least 550 (critical reading and writing); or\\r\\nPearson Test of English (PTEA) 42; or\\r\\nRMIT English Worldwide (REW) Advanced Level; or\\r\\nPass SIM English Test at Advanced 1 Level; or\\r\\nAn equivalent English language qualification.\\r\\nApplicants who do not meet the English language requirement would need to undergo the Certificate in English Language (CEL) programme before enrolment in the programme.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe duration of the CEL programme depends on the applicant\\u2019s English language proficiency level.\\r\\n\\r\\nApplicants can sit for an English Placement Test conducted by SIM to determine their English language proficiency level. Click here for details of the CEL programme\\r\\n\\r\\nNotes :\\r\\n\\r\\nIELTS or TOEFL or SAT1 or Pearson Test of English scores must be less than two years at point of enrolment.\\r\\nThe SIM English Placement Test results will be valid for one year from the date of the test.\",\"fees\":\"Course Fee\\r\\nTotal: S$3,584.50 (for 2021 intake, one-time payment before class commences).\\r\\n\\r\\nPer module: S$716.90\\r\\n\\r\\nAll fees inclusive of prevailing GST.\",\"exemptions\":\"Exemption Eligibility\\r\\nNil\",\"profiles\":\"Profiles\\r\\nLecturers and their Teaching Modules\\r\\n\\r\\nAverage teacher-student ratio 1:27\",\"assessments_exams\":\"Assessment and Exams\\r\\nEach module is assessed through multiple continuous assessments.\\r\\nContinuous assessments may include practical assessment, class tests, discussions, presentations, group and individual assignments.\\r\\n\\r\\nPromotion\\r\\nStudents must pass all the modules in the course in order to qualify for progression to Diploma in Information Technology.\\r\\n\\r\\nGraduating students will be issued a copy of the course result transcript and a certificate of completion from SIM. Graduating students will be deemed as meeting the academic requirement for entry into the Diploma in Information Technology.\\r\\n\\r\\nAttendance Requirement\\r\\n75% attendance to sit for exams.\\r\\nStudent\\u2019s Pass holders: at least 90% attendance in any month of the course (as required by the Singapore Immigration Checkpoint Authority).\\r\\n\\r\\nGraduation\\r\\nTo graduate, students must successfully complete and pass all 5 modules. Graduating students will receive a result transcript and the Certificate of Completion from SIM.\",\"entry_qualification\":\"[\\\"o level\\\"]\",\"application\":\"Full-time \\u2013 Jul 2021 Intake\\r\\nLocal Applicants\\r\\nNow till 23 May 2021\\r\\nInternational Applicants\\r\\nNow till 9 May 2021\\r\\n\\r\\nFull-time \\u2013 Oct 2021 Intake\\r\\nLocal Applicants\\r\\nNow till 22 Aug 2021\\r\\nInternational Applicants\\r\\nNow till 15 Aug 2021\",\"course_start_end_date\":\"Intake Month(s)\\r\\nFull-time: Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct\\r\\n4 intakes per year: January, April, July & October\\r\\n\\r\\nJuly intake: 1 July 2021 to 31 December 2021\\r\\nOctober intake: 1 October 2021 to 31 March 2022\",\"scholarships_award\":\"Nil\",\"overview\":\"Developed and awarded by the Singapore Institute of Management, Singapore\\r\\n\\r\\nThe 6-month programme equips you the fundamentals of computing and information technology understanding and with the necessary skills and knowledge to move on, with confidence, to progress to study at diploma level.\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/sim007217.jpg\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1616764281,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619846520,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846520),(132,21,'common\\models\\Courses','courses','update','{\"id\":21,\"school_id\":\"4\",\"name\":\"Diploma in Banking and Finance\",\"mode_of_study\":\"full_time\",\"disciplines\":\"Banking and Finance\",\"sub_disciplines\":\"Finance\",\"academic_level\":\"Diploma\",\"introduction\":\"Understanding banking & finance fundamentals\\r\\nYou acquire:\\r\\n\\r\\nA good foundation in concepts and practice in banking and finance\\r\\nAccreditation towards pursuing a Bachelor programme in this field\\r\\nFurther Education\\r\\nWith the Diploma, you can apply for advanced standing to the various degree programmes with our partner universities.\\r\\n\\r\\nPlease click here for details on the advanced standing.\\r\\n\\r\\nCareer Prospects\\r\\nGraduates may work in:\\r\\n\\r\\nFinancial services\\r\\nBanking\\r\\nInvestment management\\r\\nManagement consultancy\",\"programme_structure\":\"Teaching Faculty\\r\\nLecturers are both academic and industry-based professionals with extensive work experience and knowledge in their domain.\\r\\n\\r\\nDelivery Mode\\r\\nThe course is 100% face-to-face lecture-based learning. Coursework includes attendance at lectures, discussions of case studies, tests, presentations, and completion of group and individually-written assignments.\\r\\n\\r\\nLearning Support\\r\\nClasses and workshops are available on study skills, academic writing and presentation.\\r\\n\\r\\nAcademic Materials\\r\\nInclude module outlines, reading lists and handbooks on study strategies\\r\\n\\r\\nCurriculum\\r\\n15-month full-time programme (5 terms) of 15 modules:\\r\\n\\r\\nBusiness Accounting\\r\\nBusiness Law\\r\\nBusiness Management and Communications\\r\\nBusiness Mathematics\\r\\nBusiness Statistics\\r\\nCredit Risk Analysis and Management\\r\\nEconomics for Managers\\r\\nFinancial Markets and Institutions\\r\\nFinancial Trading\\r\\nInformation Systems for Business\\r\\nInvestment\\r\\nManaging Business Finance\\r\\nManaging Human Resources\\r\\nNegotiation and Inter-cultural Management\\r\\nPrinciples of Marketing\\r\\nContact hours: 42 hrs per module, total: 630 hrs\\r\\n\\r\\n5 terms. Each term is a period of three months.\\r\\n\\r\\nLectures at least 6 times a week (Mon-Sat)\\r\\n\\r\\nEach lesson: 3 hrs\\r\\n\\r\\nClick here for the programme schedule\\r\\n\\r\\nClick here for the module outline\\r\\n\\r\\nProgramme Calendar\\r\\n2 intakes a year in April & October, each covering 15 months.\\r\\n\\r\\nApril intake: early April to end-June (following year)\\r\\n\\r\\nOctober intake: early October to end-December (following year)\\r\\n\\r\\nCandidature Period\\r\\nMaximum allowed period to complete the 15-month programme is 30 months or 2.5 years.\\r\\n\\r\\nNo refund or recourse should the student fail to complete in the maximum period.\\r\\n\\r\\nSIM reserves the right to recommend and withdraw a student who cannot cope with the demands of the programme, especially when the student\\u2019s pass has expired.\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum Class Size\\r\\nMinimum class size: 25 students.Students will be informed within 30 days before class commences.\",\"admission_criteria\":\"Admission Criteria\\r\\nGCE A-level, IB diploma, or other equivalent pre-university certifications, or Polytechnic diploma or SIM GE\\u2019s foundation programme, namely, Management Foundation Studies (MFS)\\r\\nOther qualifications will be assessed based on the equivalence to GCE \\u2018A\\u2019 level examinations.\\r\\nApplicants who do not meet the academic requirements might be recommended to undergo a 6-month Management Foundation Studies (MFS) programme. Click here for details of the MFS programme.\\r\\n\\r\\nFor international applicants (full-time programme only)\\r\\nInternational applicants will be assessed on the qualification\\u2019s equivalent to the GCE \\u2018A\\u2019 level examinations.\\r\\n\\r\\nRefer to the details on qualifications listed in the International Student Prospectus.  Alternatively, you may click here for the list of overseas qualifications.\\r\\n\\r\\nEnglish Language Requirements\\r\\nGCE \\u2018O\\u2019 level credit pass (grade 1 to 6) in English (as first language); or\\r\\nEnglish ACT Total score of 24 with at least 20 for writing; or\\r\\nTOEFL 550 (TWE 4.0) or 59 (iBT) or 59 (iBT Home Edition); or\\r\\nIELTS 5.5; or\\r\\nPass SIM English test at Advanced 1 level; or\\r\\nSAT I 550 (critical reading & writing); or\\r\\nPearson Test of English (PTEA) 42; or\\r\\nRMIT English Worldwide (REW) Advanced Level; or\\r\\nDuolingo English Test score (DET) of 90; or\\r\\nAn equivalent English Language qualification\\r\\nApplicants who do not meet the English language requirement would need to undergo the Certificate in English Language (CEL) programme prior to enrolment in the MFS and Diploma programmes.  The duration of the CEL programme depends on the applicant\\u2019s English language proficiency level.  Applicants can sit for an English Placement Test conducted by SIM to determine their English language proficiency level.  Click here for details of the CEL programme.\\r\\n\\r\\nNotes:\\r\\n\\r\\nIELTS or TOEFL Academic scores must be less than two years at point of enrolment.\\r\\nThe SIM English Placement Test results will be valid for one year from the date of the test.\",\"fees\":\"Course Fee\\r\\nS$11,770 (For 2021 Intake) \\u2013 payable over 5 terms before class commences\\r\\n\\r\\nPer module: S$784.66\\r\\n\\r\\nApplication Fee applies\\r\\n\\r\\nAll fees inclusive of prevailing GST\",\"exemptions\":\"Exemption Eligibility\\r\\nNil\",\"profiles\":\"Academic Profiles\\r\\nLecturers & Teaching Modules\\r\\n\\r\\nAverage teacher-student ratio 1:63\\r\\n\\r\\nMinimum class size : 32\\r\\n\\r\\nMaximum class size : 79\",\"assessments_exams\":\"Assessment & Exams\\r\\nContinuous assessment and end-of-term exam.\\r\\n\\r\\nContinuous assessments include case studies, class tests, discussions, presentations, group and individual assignments.\\r\\n\\r\\nPromotion\\r\\nTo attain a pass for each module, students must achieve overall minimum GPA of 1.0 (grade D).\\r\\n\\r\\nAttendance requirement\\r\\nLocal students: 75%\\r\\nInternational students: at least 90% attendance in any month of the course (as required by the Singapore Immigration Checkpoints Authority).\\r\\n\\r\\nGraduation\\r\\nGraduating students who passed all 15 modules will be issued a transcript and awarded with a Diploma from SIM upon graduation.\",\"entry_qualification\":\"[\\\"a level\\\",\\\"diploma\\\"]\",\"application\":\"Oct 2021 Intake\\r\\nSingaporeans\\/ PR\\r\\n16 December 2020 \\u2013 22 August 2021\\r\\n\\r\\nInternational Applicants:\\r\\n16 December 2020 \\u2013 15 August 2021\\r\\n\\r\\n*  Applicants may be offered to Management Foundation Studies and\\/or Certificate in English Language Programmes according to the relevant terms.\",\"course_start_end_date\":\"Intake Month(s)\\r\\nFull-time: Apr, Oct\\r\\nIntake Month(s)\\r\\nFull-time: Apr, Oct\\r\\n2 intakes a year in April & October\\r\\n\\r\\nApril Intake: 1 April 2021 to 30 June 2022\\r\\n\\r\\nOctober intake: 1 October 2021 to 31 December 2022\\r\\n\\r\\n15-month full-time programme of 15 modules\",\"scholarships_award\":\"Nil\",\"overview\":\"This programme is developed and awarded by the Singapore Institute of Management, Singapore.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis 15-month programme is for you, if you intend to pursue a career in banking & finance, or be exposed to the financial trading environment\",\"thumbnail_url\":\"https:\\/\\/www.simge.edu.sg\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2018\\/10\\/sim007217.jpg\",\"tags\":\"\\\"\\\"\",\"notes\":\"\",\"status\":\"enabled\",\"created_at\":1619701343,\"created_by\":2,\"updated_at\":1619846539,\"updated_by\":1}',1,1619846539),(133,5,'common\\models\\Events','events','update','{\"id\":5,\"school_id\":\"1\",\"session\":\"2021Q1\",\"name\":\"Information Technology Foundation Studies (ITFS